description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Band 6 Occupational Therapist with a patient-centred approach and a passion for rehabilitation to our Chesterfield &amp; North East Derbyshire Integrated Community team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our integrated, multi-disciplinary team provides goal-focused rehabilitation to support patients in their own homes and care homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service provides 7 day cover and incorporates both a rapid response service to prevent admissions and support discharges from hospital and to provide therapy to Patients in the Community Support beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have a key role in supporting these Community Support beds and working with the patients on their return back to their own home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be an expectation that the appointed candidate will be flexible and work across the different therapy pathways to support individualised patient care, so the ability to adapt is an essential part of this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to develop your skills of specialist therapy assessment and treatment in a community setting alongside developing additional generic skills to provide a comprehensive assessment to a variety of complex patients in a residential rehabilitation unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be well supported in the role by a skilled, multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the role there will be a need for travel and transportation of equipment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a clinical employee it will be your responsibility to ensure that your behaviour and values reflect those set out in the DCHS Way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jane Saunby, Integrated Community Team Lead - Chesterfield Central, jane.saunby@nhs.net, 07747 780822&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rachael Scicluna-Penso, Integrated Community Team Lead - Bolsover, 07721 879771&lt;/p&gt;
